Thepaper reports four studies concerning attention to and comprehension of Multimedia presentations. The Multimedia sequence used was taken from a commercially produced CD-ROM, ‘The Etiology of Cancer’, First, an eye tracking study of the presentation is reported. A second study was then conducted on the recall of the materials used in the eye tracking study. The results of these studies were used to propose design guidelines for Multimedia presentations. The guidelines were applied to produce are-authored version of the original presentation. A further two studies were then conducted on the re-authored version to assess the impact of the design guidelines.